    &gt; 
    &gt; JDepend 1.4, the freely-available Java package dependency 
    &gt; analyzer,  has
    &gt; been released.  Of particular interest to JUnit users is 
    &gt; the ability to
    &gt; write tests that automatically check metrics tolerances, 
    &gt; existence of
    &gt; package dependency cycles, and package dependency constraints.
    &gt; 
    &gt; 
    &gt; New Features:
    &gt; 
    &gt; - Added package dependency constraints to support writing 
    &gt; tests that
    &gt; fail if any package dependency other than those declared in the
    &gt; dependency constraints are detected.  Refer to the 
    &gt; documentation or the
    &gt; jdepend.framework.ConstraintTest class for complete examples.
    &gt; 
    &gt;   For example, the following test case method will fail 
    &gt; if the analyzed
    &gt; packages contain any dependencies other than those declared in the
    &gt; dependency constraint:
    &gt; 
    &gt;     public void testDependencyConstraint() {
    &gt; 
    &gt;         JavaPackage ejb = new JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.ejb&quot;);
    &gt;         JavaPackage web = new JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.web&quot;);
    &gt;         JavaPackage util = new JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.util&quot;);
    &gt; 
    &gt;         ejb.dependsUpon(util);
    &gt;         web.dependsUpon(util);
    &gt; 
    &gt;         DependencyConstraint constraint = new 
    &gt; DependencyConstraint();
    &gt;         constraint.addPackage(ejb);
    &gt;         constraint.addPackage(web);
    &gt;         constraint.addPackage(util);
    &gt; 
    &gt;         _jdepend.analyze();
    &gt; 
    &gt;         assert(_jdepend.dependencyMatch(constraint));
    &gt;     }
    &gt; 
    &gt; - Added the jdepend.xmlui.JDepend class to generate 
    &gt; package metrics,
    &gt; dependencies, and cycles in an XML format for easier 
    &gt; integration with
    &gt; other tools.
    &gt; 
    &gt;   Example usage:
    &gt;       java jdepend.xmlui.JDepend -file report.xml /myproject/src
    &gt; 
    &gt; 
    &gt; The JDepend documentation is available at
    &gt; 
    &gt;        http://www.clarkware.com/software/JDepend.html
    &gt; 
    &gt; JDepend 1.4 can be downloaded directly from
    &gt; 
    &gt;        http://www.clarkware.com/software/jdepend1.4.zip
    &gt; 
    &gt; 
    &gt; Any feedback you may have is most welcome and appreciated.
